# Playwright and Desktop E2E Rules

## Test modes in this repository

- Web preview E2E uses `playwright.config.ts` and runs against `vite preview`.
- Desktop E2E uses `playwright.tauri.config.ts` and `tauri-plugin-playwright`.

## File placement

- Keep E2E specs under `e2e/`.
- Reuse shared fixtures/helpers (for example `e2e/tauri-fixtures.ts`, `e2e/axe-helpers.ts`).
- Do not duplicate setup logic already centralized in Playwright configs.

## Reliability conventions

- Prefer deterministic selectors and explicit waits via Playwright expect APIs.
- Avoid fixed sleeps unless there is no event-driven alternative.
- Mark CI-only assumptions clearly when desktop/web environments differ.

## Accessibility and smoke coverage

- Keep at least one smoke path for critical story flow.
- Reuse existing axe-based helpers for a11y checks where appropriate.

## Commands

- Web E2E: `npm run test:e2e`
- Desktop E2E: `npm run test:e2e:tauri`
- Browser install: `npm run test:e2e:install`
